dataIdInfo.idPurp: These data are suitable for representing the general orientation and position of maintained, major road features on the North Slope. Minor connections or roads within developed areas may not be represented or are generalized. Accuracy of these data is uncertain and appropriate use of these data is the responsibility of the user.
dataIdInfo.idAbs: These infrastructure data were originally compiled by Audubon in 2014 and provided to the BLM Rapid Ecological Assessment (REA) project for the North Slope region. The data were updated by the Alaska Center for Conservation Science (ACCS) for the REA and released for public distribution on the BLM/REA website. The North Slope Science Initiative (NSSI) has subsequently edited the REA product using high resolution imagery as a verification base and heads up digitizing. All locations are approximate. Neither the North Slope Science Initiative or contributors to this dataset shall be held liable for improper or incorrect use of the data described and/or contained herein. In an effort to provide the most comprehensive overview possible, we have incorporated many data sources, using a variety compilation methods. As a result there are a variety of limitations to the thematic and positional accuracy of these data.The appropriate use of these data is the responsibility of the user.
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Alaska Center for Conservation Science, North Slope Science Initiative, Alaska Department of Transportation, Alaska Division of Oil and Gas and Audubon Alaska.
